, it seems that `None` is actually a valid return value for this according to the docs at https://docs.python.org/2/library/sys.html#sys.getfilesystemencoding.\n\nThe error happens on this line when `sys.getfilesystemencoding()` returns `None` – https://github.com/mitsuhiko/click/blob/master/click/utils.py#L93 – resulting in `TypeError: decode() argument 1 must be string, not None`.\n\nI think an OK fix would be to catch both `UnicodeError` and `TypeError` on the following line, or check for `None` first and then falling back to the default case.\n\nThanks for the awesome library!\n","closed_by":{"login":"untitaker","id":837573,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjgzNzU3Mw==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/837573?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/untitaker","html_url":"https://github.com/untitaker","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/untitaker/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/untitaker/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/untitaker/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/untitaker/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/untitaker/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/untitaker/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/untitaker/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/untitaker/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/untitaker/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/pallets/click/issues/355/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/pallets/click/issues/355/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed"}